{
  "doc_id": "42108",
  "text": "TRTS is a widely used pump-probe technique to measure the dispersive AC-mobility µ e+h (f) of photo-excited charge carriers at THz frequencies, as well as the decay of the photoconductivity from femtoseconds to nanoseconds shown in Fig. 1 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The outstanding benefits of this technique include its non-destructive and contactless nature as well as high time resolutions of <100 fs. Recently TRTS was extended to be used in reflection mode [CITATION_4] and to derive mobilities for thin films on highly conductive substrates [CITATION_5] .",
